## 2. Detailed Job Applications and Requirements

### 1. WorkBetterNow — AI Software Developer (Internal Tools)
* **Company & Title:** WorkBetterNow — AI Software Developer (Internal Tools)
* **Direct Application Link:** [Zoho Recruit Portal](https://workbetternow.zohorecruit.com/jobs/Careers/746650000037462674/AI-Software-Developer-Internal-Tools)
* **Direct Job Post Link:** [Remotive Post](https://remotive.com/remote/jobs/artificial-intelligence/ai-software-developer-5058144)
* **Salary & Benefits:** 
  - **Salary:** Starts at $1,200 per month (as specified in the application screening questions).
  - **Benefits:** 100% remote work, 18 paid vacation days + U.S. federal holidays, paid maternity/paternity leave (up to 2 months with 50% salary coverage after 1 year), supportive environment, 2 in-person team gatherings per year in your local city, training/development support.
  - **Work Hours:** 9:00 am – 6:00 pm EST/CST/MST/PST (including a 1-hour lunch break).
* **Job Description Summary:** 
  The AI Software Developer designs, builds, and ships internal applications that streamline operations, reduce software licensing costs, and scale with business growth. Using AI-assisted development tools (Replit, Claude Code, Copilot), the developer rapidly prototypes and delivers production-ready tools that replace third-party software and manual workflows.
* **Core Responsibilities:**
  - Build, ship, and maintain internal web applications using AI-assisted development environments (Replit, Claude Code, Copilot).
  - Partner with leadership to identify high-cost or underused software to replace with purpose-built internal tools; estimate cost savings.
  - Write clean, documented, and maintainable code following source control and deployment best practices; apply security/data protection standards.
  - Collaborate with stakeholders across departments to scope, prioritize, and demo new tools; maintain a transparent backlog and document tools.
  - Stay current on AI development tools and report on delivery KPIs (tools shipped, cost savings, adoption, uptime).
* **Tech Stack, Qualifications & Technical Requirements:**
  - **Languages/Frameworks:** JavaScript/TypeScript, React, Node.js, Python.
  - **SaaS Integrations:** REST APIs connecting to platforms like HubSpot, Microsoft 365, SharePoint, or Zoho Recruit.
  - **Methodologies:** Scrum/Agile frameworks, sprint planning, standups, iterative delivery.
  - **Location:** Live in LATAM or the Caribbean.
  - **English Fluency:** Fluent (written and spoken) to communicate with US-based teams.
  - **System Requirements:** Intel 11th Gen / AMD Ryzen 5000 series (Windows) or Apple M2 (Mac); minimum 16 GB RAM; stable internet connection of 25-50 Mbps.
  - **Experience:** 3+ years of building and shipping web applications with a track record of delivering working software quickly.
  - **Preferred:** Experience replacing paid SaaS with custom-built tools; containerization experience (Docker/Kubernetes).
* **Specific Submission Requirements & Screening Questions:**
  - **File Uploads:** 
    - English Resume/CV (formats: .doc, .docx, .pdf, .odt, .rtf).
    - EFSET Certificate (obtained via a free 15-minute test at www.efset.org/quick-check/).
    - Specs Screenshot (showing RAM and processor. Mac: Apple menu > About This Mac; Windows: Settings > System > About).
    - College or University Degree (Optional).
  - **Screening Questions:**
    1. Confirm you live in LATAM or the Caribbean (permanent residents only; dual/sole US citizens not eligible).
    2. Full legal name, email, and phone number (agree to receive WhatsApp updates).
    3. Date of birth (MM/DD/YYYY).
    4. System specs confirmation: Intel 11th Gen/Ryzen 5000/M2 Mac, 25+ Mbps internet, and headset.
    5. Select exact RAM from multi-choice.
    6. Confirm starting salary of $1,200/month is within expectations.
    7. Describe your last position, responsibilities, and reason for leaving (max 999 characters).
    8. Enter exact EFSET score.
    9. Confirm local bank or Payoneer account to receive payments.
    10. Platform familiarity multi-select checklist.

#### Customized Recommendations for Juan Jaramillo:
* **Positioning & Fit:** 100% fit on location (Bogotá, Colombia is in LATAM) and system requirements (Juan owns a modern Mac matching the requirements). Juan's background of building internal SaaS solutions at TopNetworks (EmailGenius, TrafficGenius) is a perfect match for "replacing paid SaaS with custom internal tools".
* **Resume Variant:** Use the **Vibe Coding & AI-Native Engineering** resume. It emphasizes rapid, iterative AI-assisted development (Claude Code, GitHub Copilot) and fits the "rapid prototyping" ethos of this role perfectly.
* **Screening Questions Strategy:**
  - *Salary:* Although Juan's target is $3,500 - $4,500, if he wishes to secure this role as a stable contract stream, he must check "Yes" to confirm the $1,200/month expectation. He can position himself as an incredibly high-ROI hire who can build complex tools in a quarter of the normal time.
  - *Last Position Essay (Max 999 chars):* Draft a response highlighting his role as AI Development Lead at TopNetworks: "As AI Development Lead at TopNetworks, I designed, built, and shipped several internal SaaS tools (EmailGenius, TrafficGenius, RouteGenius) that replaced expensive third-party subscriptions. I utilized Next.js 15, TypeScript, Python, and Vertex AI. I led rapid prototyping using AI-assisted environments (Cursor, Copilot), which significantly reduced engineering time and software licensing costs."
  - *English Test:* Complete the 15-minute EFSET test immediately. Juan’s professional English is highly advanced; obtaining a C1/C2 certificate will be a strong validation signal.

